# Meeting Notes — 3/17

## Summary
Eric indirectly rejected the idea of using ProcessBuilder (running the Java program in a separate process).

However, he pointed us to a relevant GitHub repository:
- https://github.com/fniephaus/graalpy-spring-boot-summarize?tab=readme-ov-file

This repo appears to implement something similar to what we are trying to build, but:
- It uses a smaller, non-docking-style library
- It is built with Spring Boot
- It uses **markitdown**, which is a lightweight alternative to **docling** (associated with Microsoft)

## Idea (Nick)
